  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      In this study, participants with Stage IB/II-IIIA non-small cell lung cancer (NSCLC) who
      have undergone surgical resection (lobectomy or pneumonectomy) with or without adjuvant
      chemotherapy will be treated with pembrolizumab or placebo. The primary study hypothesis is
      that pembrolizumab will provide improved disease-free survival (DFS) versus placebo.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
